[SN]TITLE[SN]
Retired Halifax seamstress in £4m Lotto win

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A retired seamstress who won more than £4m on the lottery said her first purchase following her success was a pair of slippers and some cheese.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
25 June 2015 Last updated at 19:03 BST
Jane Lewis, 69, from Halifax, won £4,301,108 on the June 17 Lotto draw.
Mrs Lewis scooped the prize after opting for a lucky dip ticket rather than playing her usual numbers.
